&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–5 years of hands-on experience in mechanical or product development engineering&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience contributing to hardware products through development and/or early production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid foundation in engineering fundamentals, including materials, mechanics, and basic failure modes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of common volume manufacturing processes (e.g., injection molding, machining, sheet metal) and their design considerations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in CAD and creating clear, accurate drawings; exposure to GD&amp;amp;T is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with prototyping and iterative design (e.g., 3D printing, laser cutting, quick-turn fabrication).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to approach problems methodically, apply sound engineering judgment, and seek guidance when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
